Hello Todd  Did you use a timing light to set the timing?? where did  you set 
it? If it is too high tjhen this could cause both overheating and  dieseling. 
Also check and make sure your throttle cable is set right. on the  
progressive webers if the throttle doesn't close all the way then they will  diesel. Get 
some temp gages, I would install both oil and head temp ones   later  mark d



